	 <title>System.ToDecimal</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para><symbol>Integer</symbol>, <symbol>Long</symbol>,
		  <symbol>Money</symbol>, and <symbol>String</symbol> types can be explicitly
		  converted to <symbol>Decimal</symbol> type using this operator.</para> 
	 <para>With strings, converts the specified <symbol>String</symbol>
		  representation of a number, with optional sign, to an equivalent 96-bit signed
		  integer.</para> 
	 <para>An error will occur if the value is outside that range of a
		  <symbol>Decimal</symbol> (-79,228,162,514,264,337,593,543,950,335 to
		  +79,228,162,514,264,337,593,543,950,335).</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select ToDecimal($357/84);
select ToDecimal("87.14");
select ToDecimal(193);</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>4.25
87.14
193</programlisting> 
	 </example> 
